# Next.js Conventions

## App Router
- Use `app/` directory structure
- Use `page.tsx` for routes, `layout.tsx` for shared layouts
- Use `loading.tsx` for loading states, `error.tsx` for error boundaries

## Data & Routing
- Prefer Server Components for data fetching (no useEffect for initial load)
- Use `generateMetadata` for dynamic page metadata
- Use route groups `(folder)` for organization without affecting URLs

## File Naming
- `page.tsx` — route page
- `layout.tsx` — layout wrapper
- `loading.tsx` — loading UI
- `error.tsx` — error boundary
- `not-found.tsx` — 404 page
